    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-10T10:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-10T10:45:00-05:00" n="565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">417.00/493: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-10T10:00:00-05:45"
                            >March 10, 1934—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. New law has gone into effect extending time limit for presenting claims to
                    Nicaraguan Claims Commission until April 30, 1934. Full text follows by air
                        mail.<note n="89" xml:id="d565fn89">For text of the law, signed by the
                        President February 20, 1934, see <hi rend="italic">La Gaceta-Diario
                            Oficial</hi>, March 8, 1934, p. 457.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
